an class=title> Re: nothing in EQ has...</span><hr size=1> Totally agree with you Aludarus, I've lost interest playing my druid and I don't fancy levelling another character just because VI have neglected us. Although I could use my 60 druid to power level another char, why should I spend weeks and more money for another account just get around the problem. EQ is ageing rapidly for me, even the new expansion and the thought of yet more gruelling xp grinds to level has zero appeal for me. I think VI totally screwed up via lack of thought and tallent when all they could do to extend eq's life was to make encounters more and more difficult, requiring an obscene amount of people and coordination to even attempt a mob let alone any CR from it. The game is old and the content is stale, new mobs/items are just a regig of the numbers, the only thing that keeps most people loggin in is the friends they've made. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukinare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/4/02 3:41:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=633.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: nothing in EQ has...</span><hr size=1> This does not seem in line with the intended role of the beastlord. Why would they have a mana regen buff? They are often compared as shaman (with stronger pets) monks. Shamans do not have mana regen, and monks certainly do not.<br><br>I think they are just tossing in mana regen buffs to anyone who can cast just to quit people from bitching. Apparently the opposite is true.<br><br>While I disagree that beastlords should get our role as POTG caster (which is essentially what they did) if they do not have this spell, all they are is a glorified mod rod carrier. <p><center><img src=http://members.cox.net/katemartin13/xorkin2.jpg><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18482>Venerable Kinare Hersbrucker, Hierophant of Tunare</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18478>Venerable Xorena V'Deers, High Priestess of Innoruuk</a> <br>Proud member of <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bcrimsonblades28252>Crimson Blades</a> on Rodcet Nife<br>215 skill tailor <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=214.topic>looking for work</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/4/02 4:03:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=633.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: nothing in EQ has...</span><hr size=1> <i>Shamans do not have mana regen</i><br><br>Not in the form of spells, no, but they can make "clarity potions" at great cost, and if you have some pp to burn, you can buy those. If you count cannabalize as mana regen, then yes, shamans have mana regen. <br><br><i>This does not seem in line with the intended role of the beastlord. Why would they have a mana regen buff?</i><br><br>It's only 3 per tick. But the question is, does it stack with other casters' self-mana-regen buffs? <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uylana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/php-bin/shared/images/icons/evileye.gif" B